President Obama has announced his intent to appoint several individuals to the National Council on Federal Labor-Management Relations. The Council, created in 2009 by Executive Order, advises the President on matters involving labor-management relations in the executive branch. The Council is co-chaired by the Director of the Office of Personnel Management, John Berry, and the Deputy Director for Management of the Office of Management and Budget, Jeffrey Zients. The Chair of the Federal Labor Relations Authority, Carol Pope, is also an ex-officio member. The President has designated several other individuals to the Council, including Deputy Secretaries from various departments. The appointed individuals have diverse backgrounds and experience in labor and government. President Obama expressed his gratitude for their counsel and looks forward to continuing the dialogue with them.